                    <p>
                        Thread count refers to the number of threads woven into one square inch of fabric, and it’s often marketed as a measure of quality. But higher isn’t always better.

                        200–400: Ideal for most cotton sheets. Lightweight and breathable.

                        400–600: A bit heavier and softer, perfect for cooler climates or a cozy feel.

                        600+: Can be very luxurious, but beware—some manufacturers inflate thread counts artificially by using multi-ply yarns.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        Linen is made from the flax plant and is perfect for hot climates due to its breathability and moisture-wicking properties. It softens with each wash and has a unique, slightly textured feel.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        Bamboo sheets are eco-friendly, hypoallergenic, and naturally breathable. They feel silky soft, much like a blend between cotton and silk.
                    </p>

